-- Hong Kong shares edge up, led by China Mobile
-- By Chen Yixin and the Shanghai Newsroom
-- Mon Oct 13, 2014 04:10AM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, Oct 13 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares erased morning losses on Monday due to strength in blue-chip stocks led by China Mobile, which rose after signing a business deal with Deutche Telekom.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> ended up 0.2 percent at 23,143.38 points. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong fell 0.2 percent. China Mobile <0941.HK> gained 1.8 percent, following a agreement it signed with Deutsche Telekom <DTEGn.DE> on Friday to create a platform for so-called connected cars in China. [ID:nL6N0S44JR]